{"type":"section","nativeType":"section","number":"8695","heading":"Navy battle force ship assessment and requirement reporting","label":"8695 Navy battle force ship assessment and requirement reporting","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s8695","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t10/stC/ptIV/ch863","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft10%2Fs8695","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":["Editorial Notes","Amendments2023—Subsec. (e). substituted “Responsibilities of Commandant of Marine Corps” for “Amphibious Warfare Ships” in heading and inserted “and for naval vessels with the primary mission of transporting Marines” before period at end.Pub. L. 118–312022—Subsec. (e). added subsec. (e).Pub. L. 117–263","Statutory Notes and Related Subsidiaries","Baseline Assessment and Requirement Required, , , provided that:Pub. L. 117–81, div. A, title X, § 1017(c)135 Stat. 1897Dec. 27, 2021“The date of the enactment of this Act [] is deemed to be a covered event for the purposes of establishing a baseline battle force ship assessment and requirement under , United States Code, as added by subsection (a) [enacting this section].”Dec. 27, 2021section 8695 of title 10"],"amendments":["Amendments2023—Subsec. (e). substituted “Responsibilities of Commandant of Marine Corps” for “Amphibious Warfare Ships” in heading and inserted “and for naval vessels with the primary mission of transporting Marines” before period at end.Pub. L. 118–312022—Subsec. (e). added subsec. (e).Pub. L. 117–263","Baseline Assessment and Requirement Required, , , provided that:Pub. L. 117–81, div. A, title X, § 1017(c)135 Stat. 1897Dec. 27, 2021“The date of the enactment of this Act [] is deemed to be a covered event for the purposes of establishing a baseline battle force ship assessment and requirement under , United States Code, as added by subsection (a) [enacting this section].”Dec. 27, 2021section 8695 of title 10"],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"subsection","nativeType":"subsection","number":"a","heading":".—In General","label":"a .—In General","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s8695/a","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t10/s8695","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft10%2Fs8695%2Fa","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"Not later than 180 days after the date on which a covered event occurs, the Chief of Naval Operations shall submit to the congressional defense committees a battle force ship assessment and requirement.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subsection","nativeType":"subsection","number":"b","heading":".—Assessment","label":"b .—Assessment","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s8695/b","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t10/s8695","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft10%2Fs8695%2Fb","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"1","heading":null,"label":"1","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s8695/b/1","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t10/s8695/b","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft10%2Fs8695%2Fb%2F1","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"A review of the strategic guidance of the Federal Government, the Department of Defense, and the Navy for identifying priorities, missions, objectives, and principles, in effect as of the date on which the assessment is submitted, that the force structure of the Navy must follow.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"2","heading":null,"label":"2","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s8695/b/2","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t10/s8695/b","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft10%2Fs8695%2Fb%2F2","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"An identification of the steady-state demand for maritime security and security force assistance activities.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"3","heading":null,"label":"3","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s8695/b/3","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t10/s8695/b","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft10%2Fs8695%2Fb%2F3","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"An identification of the force options that can satisfy the steady-state demands for activities required by theater campaign plans of combatant commanders.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"4","heading":null,"label":"4","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s8695/b/4","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t10/s8695/b","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft10%2Fs8695%2Fb%2F4","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"A force optimization analysis that produces a day-to-day global posture required to accomplish peacetime and steady-state tasks assigned by combatant commanders.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"5","heading":null,"label":"5","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s8695/b/5","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t10/s8695/b","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft10%2Fs8695%2Fb%2F5","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"A modeling of the ability of the force to fight and win scenarios approved by the Department of Defense.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"6","heading":null,"label":"6","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s8695/b/6","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t10/s8695/b","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft10%2Fs8695%2Fb%2F6","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"A calculation of the number and global posture of each force element required to meet steady-state presence demands and warfighting response timelines.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]}]},{"type":"subsection","nativeType":"subsection","number":"c","heading":".—Requirement","label":"c .—Requirement","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s8695/c","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t10/s8695","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft10%2Fs8695%2Fc","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"1","heading":null,"label":"1","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s8695/c/1","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t10/s8695/c","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft10%2Fs8695%2Fc%2F1","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"A","heading":null,"label":"A","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s8695/c/1/A","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t10/s8695/c/1","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft10%2Fs8695%2Fc%2F1%2FA","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"be based on the assessment required by subsection (b); and","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"B","heading":null,"label":"B","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s8695/c/1/B","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t10/s8695/c/1","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft10%2Fs8695%2Fc%2F1%2FB","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"clause","nativeType":"clause","number":"i","heading":null,"label":"i","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s8695/c/1/B/i","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t10/s8695/c/1/B","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft10%2Fs8695%2Fc%2F1%2FB%2Fi","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"the total number of battle force ships required;","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"clause","nativeType":"clause","number":"ii","heading":null,"label":"ii","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s8695/c/1/B/ii","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t10/s8695/c/1/B","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft10%2Fs8695%2Fc%2F1%2FB%2Fii","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"the number of battle force ships required in each of the categories described in paragraph (2);","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"clause","nativeType":"clause","number":"iii","heading":null,"label":"iii","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s8695/c/1/B/iii","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t10/s8695/c/1/B","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft10%2Fs8695%2Fc%2F1%2FB%2Fiii","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"the classes of battle force ships included in each of the categories described in paragraph (2); and","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"clause","nativeType":"clause","number":"iv","heading":null,"label":"iv","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s8695/c/1/B/iv","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t10/s8695/c/1/B","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft10%2Fs8695%2Fc%2F1%2FB%2Fiv","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"the number of battle force ships required in each class.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]}]}]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"2","heading":null,"label":"2","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s8695/c/2","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t10/s8695/c","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft10%2Fs8695%2Fc%2F2","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"A","heading":null,"label":"A","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s8695/c/2/A","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t10/s8695/c/2","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft10%2Fs8695%2Fc%2F2%2FA","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"Aircraft carriers.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagr